section.section:
All summonses shall be served by the sheriff, except that:
In the City of Annapolis, summonses may also be served by the Annapolis Police Department;
In Anne Arundel County, summonses may also be served by inspectors employed by the Board and by the Anne Arundel County Police Department;
In Baltimore City, summonses may also be served by inspectors employed by the Board of Liquor License Commissioners for Baltimore City;
In Cecil County, summonses may also be served by inspectors employed by the Cecil County Board of License Commissioners;
In Dorchester County, summonses may also be served by the inspector employed by Dorchester County and assigned to the Board of License Commissioners; and
In Harford County, summonses may also be served by inspectors employed by the Harford County Liquor Control Board.

This subsection applies in the following counties:
Anne Arundel County;
Baltimore City;
Baltimore County;
Carroll County;
Cecil County;
Frederick County;
Garrett County;
Howard County;
Prince George's County;
Wicomico County; and
Worcester County.
